604
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:58,080
It's a wonderful piece.

605
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,680
Next, it's Kawakita's bowl.

606
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,560
Yours is lovely too.

607
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:05,560
- It's so cute!
- It's nice. Very good.

608
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:09,320
Kawakita's bowl
resembles flower petals.

609
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,240
- So cute.
- So cute.

610
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:13,120
It will wrap softly
around anything you put in.

611
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,280
What a gentle bowl.

612
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,960
- Now, I'll take out Madame's pot.
- Okay.

613
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:20,040
Oh, no! I'm so nervous.

614
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,920
It was fired at quite a risky place.

615
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,480
What is the result?

616
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,880
Here.

617
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,280
- Here.
- Amazing!

618
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:31,360
It's lovely!

619
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:33,160
It's so lovely!

620
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,800
Like one you can buy.

621
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:38,080
The pot Madame made
with all her might is done.

622
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:39,040
Thank goodness.

623
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:40,720
The part that looks like droplets

624
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:43,120
is glass that formed
when ash melted.

625
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:47,920
The scarlet colour and gradation
are beautiful.

626
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,320
It's so beautiful!

627
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:51,800
I'm so impressed.

628
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,040
I'm touched.

629
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:57,120
The last thing Mr Kanzaki
takes out is...

630
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,960
Wait, what...

631
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:02,920
Amazing!

632
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,120
A miracle happened!

633
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:07,280
A pot is stuck to Degawa Frog!

634
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,680
Whose pot is it?

635
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,840
Isn't it mine?

636
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,120
It became a joint effort!

637
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,520
- This is so cute!
- Amazing!

638
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:18,320
Made by Hotta and Tani,
Degawa Pot Frog.

639
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,880
- Amazing.
- So cute.

640
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:23,440
A miraculous collaboration was done
in the over 1,200-degree kiln.

641
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:25,200
- Amazing!
- Why?

642
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,760
Besides these,

643
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:30,040
